Write an SQL Query

Problem Statement:
Find the total number of employees and average salary for each department from the employees table.

Table Schema: Employees

| Column Name       | Data Type | Description                           |
| ----------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------- |
| emp_id            | INT       | Unique employee ID                    |
| emp_name          | VARCHAR   | Name of the employee                  |
| department        | VARCHAR   | Department of employee                |
| salary            | INT       | Salary of the employee                |


Sample Input

|emp_id	|emp_name	|department |	salary  |
|-------|---------|----------|----------|
| 1	    | Hitesh	| IT	     | 70000    |
| 2	    | Ankit	  | HR	     | 50000    | 
| 3	    | Rahul	  | IT	     | 80000    |
| 4     |	Priya  	| Finance	 | 60000    |
| 5	    | Mohit	  | HR    	 | 55000    |
| 6	    | Suresh  | IT       | 90000    |

Write an SQL query to calculate:
1) Total number of employees in each department
2) Average salary of employees in each department

Expected Output:

|department | total_employees | avg_salary |
|---------- | --------------- | ---------- |
| IT	      | 3               |	80000      |
| HR	      | 2	              | 52500      |
| Finance	  | 1	              | 60000      |

Solution

SELECT 
    department,
    COUNT(*) AS total_employees,
    AVG(salary) AS avg_salary
FROM employees
GROUP BY department;
